A devastating blast at the Hilton hotel in Taba, Egypt, killed or wounded over 100 people, including at least 23 Israelis.
Suspected car bombs targeted tourists in the Sinai desert, with explosions also reported in nearby tourist camps.
Israeli officials warned of possible attacks in the region, urging Israelis to evacuate.
Despite ongoing security alerts, many Israelis continued to visit Sinai resorts.
The explosions, believed to be caused by car bombs, led to chaos and carnage, prompting Israeli authorities to assist in evacuations and rescue efforts.
The situation remains tense as investigations into the attacks continue.
